\f1\fs24 \cf3 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f2\i\b Note:
\f1\i0\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28  You can immediately tell which documents have snapshots associated with them because their icons have dog-eared corners.\cell \lastrow\row
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 To see what\'92s changed in the document since the snapshot was taken, click on \'93Compare\'94. Try that now:\
\pard\tx560\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Type some text on the line below (anything you want):\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\tx560\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Delete the text in the following line:\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 DELETE ME!\
\pard\tx560\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Now:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}In the inspector, select the snapshot you took a moment ago.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Click \'93Compare\'94. See what happens?\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\li1440\fi-1440\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	
\f3 \uc0\u8259 
\f0 	}Text that has been added to the document since the snapshot was taken appears underlined and in blue.\
{\listtext	
\f3 \uc0\u8259 
\f0 	}Text that has been deleted appears struck out and in red.\
{\listtext	
\f3 \uc0\u8259 
\f0 	}Note that the comparison only shows 
\i textual
\i0  changes\'97it does not show changes to the formatting.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Click on the left and right arrows at the top of the inspector, next to the gear button, to navigate between the changes.\

